Relations between the US and Germany are burdened by the claims that the NSA has intercepted Chancellor Angela Merkel's mobile phone.
Thomas Oppermann, the MP who heads the parliamentary committee responsible for intelligence, said that the opportunity should be taken to listen to Snowden as a witness if this was possible 'without jeopardising him and ruining relations with the United States completely'.
Ströbele, a Green MEP, published a picture of himself and Snowden in his Twitter feed.
He was accompanied by two German journalists during his visit to Russia.
