Bulgarian consumers receive gas from South Stream at discounted rates when the entire project goes into operation in 2015.
According to Gazprom, construction work in other downstream countries is scheduled to start at the end of the year on the planned route.
The pipeline is designed for an annual capacity of 62.3 billion cubic meters of natural gas.
